			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: [WoW] Talents &amp; Auction House System w/Comments<a name="51581"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 13 04 3:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Fires of Heaven was what originally turned me on to WoW. Reading about Furor's trips to Blizzard headquarters to see alpha testing really interested me. The way he explained it really got me into it.
<br />

<br />
Most people I've talked to that have problems with World of Warcraft say that they have a problem with the cartoony graphics. While not on the Zelda: Windwaker level of cartoony, I do concede that the graphics are more cartoony than that of Everquest's. If you look at the roots of gaming, games weren't intended to exhibit realism. On the contrary, they were an escape from reality. World of Warcraft's graphics are fine once you get used to them.
<br />

<br />
As for an inferior MMORPG, I couldn't agree less. I've played beta, and the gameplay is even more addicting than Everquest's was when I first started playing it. Also, as of today, I've yet to find a bug. I won't go into specifics, but I will include some reference sites that may be more adequate at convincing you that WoW is <i>not</i> an inferior MMORPG. All I ask is that you look at World of Warcraft in its entirety before forming a negative opinion on it. I've witnessed it happening too many times before.
<br />

<br />
Another reason that I think World of Warcraft will be great is that it is made by gamers. Much of the developing staff is comprised of previous Everquest players, such as Tigole of Legacy of Steel. Also, it's no coincidence that many of the World of Warcraft beta testers are from high-end Everquest guilds.
<br />

<br />
I don't personally like the way Sony Online Entertainment has been doing their games lately. The last few Everquest expansions have just been a fluke. Planetside, Everquest Online Adventures, and Star Wars Galaxies didn't impress me much either. I've got to hand one thing to Sony though: the graphics of the games that they create are among the best I've seen.
<br />

<br />
Sony has been making a change lately from what I've seen. If John Smedley goes through with what he's been doing lately I could envision Everquest II to be a pretty solid MMORPG.
<br />

<br />
Here are links that really got me into WoW:
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://www.worldofwarcraft.com">http://www.worldofwarcraft.com</a>
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://www.blizzard.com/wow">http://www.blizzard.com/wow</a>
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://www.fohguild.org">http://www.fohguild.org</a>
<br />
Blizzard probably has more info on World of Warcraft's beta progress than all SOE games combined on their website.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
