<br />
That is opposed to the typical EQ1 addict, who craves HOURS AND HOURS of monotonous game-play...  Who cannot progress his character unless he endured those hours of torment.  Some examples:
<br />

<br />
**The Vex Thal key quest
<br />
**Phinny and his damned spine (setting your alarm and getting up every twelve hours to kill him AGAIN for four days straight)
<br />
**Killing Eldrig's PH for SIX HOURS only to give up and go to bed
<br />

<br />
The list could go on and on.  And do these things actually test your knowledge or skill?  NOPE.  Only your ability to endure hours of drudgery for the sake of your toon or guild.
<br />

<br />
I am truly hoping that eq2, or SOMETHING out there caters to the &quot;casual&quot;  --- I prefer to call it &quot;time-restricted&quot;--- player who does NOT want monotonous game play.
<br />

<br />
I want to log on for my hour or two on Tuesday and Thursday evenings, and actually ACCOMPLISH something fun and exciting in those couple of hours.  LDoN was the best thing that ever happened to these so-called &quot;casual&quot; players, imo.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, imo, eq2 shows a lot of promise to be a VERY cool game.  It remains to be seen, of course, how the AI will work, how much variety there actually will be between subclasses etc. whether the Archetype system truly WILL make it possible for everyone to get a group easily, and not wait forever cause they are just &quot;another dps&quot; class etc.  
<br />

<br />
We will see.  I'm looking forward to finding out first hand!</span></td>
