				<td colspan="2"><span>Been doing WoW beta for awhile now, and I must admit it is one h*ll of a game.  Granted there is nothing all that original with the game.  At least nothing that cannot be found someplace else in one form or another.   However WoW does have a few things going for it.  A quest system that works, is enjoyable, and make you look forward to finding more of them.  In WoW about 60% of the exp you make at any given level will gotten via quests.  The are well put together and tell a story.  
<br />

<br />
EQ has lot  of worthless quests that the reward is hardly worth time they  take to complete.  DAOC really didn't have quests.  SWG... well will not go there this was a doomed games before it even hit the shelves.
<br />

<br />
Will I move from EQ to WoW most likely not.  However this has nothing to do with EQ being better.  WoW is a MUCH better game than EQ will ever become.  Mainly because of all the uncorrectable mistakes SoE has made in the past that cannot be fixed (caugh trade skills).  
<br />

<br />
EQ2 is not for the raider... SOE has already stated this.  WoW caters to both markets and in my eyes does it well.  Either way the game is not finished and they are making improvements every day.  Bug fixes have been fairly quick too.  Heck one class but I reported last week got resolved in 2 days... granted it was a nasty bug.  Though 2 days is still a nice reponse time.  Heck in EQ you can wait that long on some petitions!</span></td>
